## Keel architecture context

This repository uses [Keel](https://github.com/zeezou17/keel) for living software architecture.

Before making structural changes, read:
- `.keel/architecture/` — C4 diagrams (C1 context, C2 containers, C3 components)
- `.keel/requirements/` — requirements linked to architecture nodes
- `.keel/decisions/` — architecture decision records (ADRs)
- `.keel/characteristics/` — quality characteristics and fitness functions
- `.keel/specs/` — work packages for implementation

Keep architecture files current when you add, move, or rename code. Node `paths` globs in `.keel/architecture/*.json` are used for drift detection.
